narrative.title: Provider Overview
narrative.text: County of Santa Clara is a Clinic/Center  Federally Qualified Health Center (FQHC) provider based in San Jose, CA. From the 2018–2024 period, this provider received $102.0M in Medicaid payments across 1.1M claims.

narrative.title: Important Context
items: This is a government entity that may serve as a fiscal agent for large populations. Government providers often bill at high volumes due to the scale of public programs they administer.

narrative.title: Why This Matters
narrative.text: This provider received $102.0M in taxpayer-funded Medicaid payments — enough to fund healthcare for approximately 12,746 Medicaid beneficiaries for a full year at average per-enrollee costs.
